defs.docs: Random number generation traits

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Error type of random number generators

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct from any type supporting `std::error::Error`
 
 Available only when configured with `std`.
 
 See also `From<NonZeroU32>`, which is available with and without `std`.

defs.name: inner
defs.docs:
Reference the inner error (`std` only)
 
 When configured with `std`, this is a trivial operation and never
 panics. Without `std`, this method is simply unavailable.

defs.name: take_inner
defs.docs:
Unwrap the inner error (`std` only)
 
 When configured with `std`, this is a trivial operation and never
 panics. Without `std`, this method is simply unavailable.

defs.name: INTERNAL_START
defs.docs:
Codes below this point represent OS Errors (i.e. positive i32 values).
 Codes at or above this point, but below [`Error::CUSTOM_START`] are
 reserved for use by the `rand` and `getrandom` crates.

defs.name: CUSTOM_START
defs.docs:
Codes at or above this point can be used by users to define their own
 custom errors.

defs.name: raw_os_error
defs.docs: Extract the raw OS error code (if this error came from the OS)

defs.name: code
defs.docs:
Retrieve the error code, if any.
 
 If this `Error` was constructed via `From<NonZeroU32>`, then this method
 will return this `NonZeroU32` code (for `no_std` this is always the
 case). Otherwise, this method will return `None`.

defs.name: block
defs.docs: The `BlockRngCore` trait and implementation helpers

defs.name: BlockRngCore
defs.docs:
A trait for RNGs which do not generate random numbers individually, but in
 blocks (typically `[u32; N]`). This technique is commonly used by
 cryptographic RNGs to improve performance.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: Results element type, e.g. `u32`.

defs.name: Results
defs.docs:
Results type. This is the 'block' an RNG implementing `BlockRngCore`
 generates, which will usually be an array like `[u32; 16]`.

defs.name: generate
defs.docs: Generate a new block of results.

defs.name: BlockRng
defs.docs:
A wrapper type implementing [`RngCore`] for some type implementing
 [`BlockRngCore`] with `u32` array buffer; i.e. this can be used to implement
 a full RNG from just a `generate` function.

defs.name: core
defs.docs: The *core* part of the RNG, implementing the `generate` function.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `BlockRng` from an existing RNG implementing
 `BlockRngCore`. Results will be generated on first use.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: Get the index into the result buffer.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs:
Reset the number of available results.
 This will force a new set of results to be generated on next use.

defs.name: generate_and_set
defs.docs:
Generate a new set of results immediately, setting the index to the
 given value.

defs.name: BlockRng64
defs.docs:
A wrapper type implementing [`RngCore`] for some type implementing
 [`BlockRngCore`] with `u64` array buffer; i.e. this can be used to implement
 a full RNG from just a `generate` function.

defs.name: core
defs.docs: The *core* part of the RNG, implementing the `generate` function.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `BlockRng` from an existing RNG implementing
 `BlockRngCore`. Results will be generated on first use.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: Get the index into the result buffer.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs:
Reset the number of available results.
 This will force a new set of results to be generated on next use.

defs.name: generate_and_set
defs.docs:
Generate a new set of results immediately, setting the index to the
 given value.

defs.name: impls
defs.docs: Helper functions for implementing `RngCore` functions.

defs.name: next_u64_via_u32
defs.docs: Implement `next_u64` via `next_u32`, little-endian order.

defs.name: fill_bytes_via_next
defs.docs: Implement `fill_bytes` via `next_u64` and `next_u32`, little-endian order.

defs.name: fill_via_u32_chunks
defs.docs:
Implement `fill_bytes` by reading chunks from the output buffer of a block
 based RNG.

defs.name: fill_via_u64_chunks
defs.docs:
Implement `fill_bytes` by reading chunks from the output buffer of a block
 based RNG.

defs.name: next_u32_via_fill
defs.docs: Implement `next_u32` via `fill_bytes`, little-endian order.

defs.name: next_u64_via_fill
defs.docs: Implement `next_u64` via `fill_bytes`, little-endian order.

defs.name: le
defs.docs:
Little-Endian utilities
 
 Little-Endian order has been chosen for internal usage; this makes some
 useful functions available.

defs.name: read_u32_into
defs.docs:
Reads unsigned 32 bit integers from `src` into `dst`.
 Borrowed from the `byteorder` crate.

defs.name: read_u64_into
defs.docs:
Reads unsigned 64 bit integers from `src` into `dst`.
 Borrowed from the `byteorder` crate.

A random number generator that retrieves randomness from from the
 operating system.

defs.name: CryptoRng
defs.docs:
A marker trait used to indicate that an [`RngCore`] or [`BlockRngCore`]
 implementation is supposed to be cryptographically secure.

defs.name: SeedableRng
defs.docs: A random number generator that can be explicitly seeded.

defs.name: Seed
defs.docs:
Seed type, which is restricted to types mutably-dereferencable as `u8`
 arrays (we recommend `[u8; N]` for some `N`).

defs.name: from_seed
defs.docs: Create a new PRNG using the given seed.

defs.name: seed_from_u64
defs.docs: Create a new PRNG using a `u64` seed.

defs.name: from_rng
defs.docs: Create a new PRNG seeded from another `Rng`.

defs.name: from_entropy
defs.docs: Creates a new instance of the RNG seeded via [`getrandom`].
